Arizona Territory (1863-02-24)

1863/02/24 -> 1866/05/04

The United States created  Arizona Territory from the western portion of New Mexico Territory and a part of present Nevada.

(U.S. Stat., vol. 12, ch. 56[1863]/pp. 664-665; Ariz. Terr. Laws 1864, 1st assy./ pp. vii-viii; Van Zandt, 162)
